<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know the inner north corridor well and understand the buyer profile that targets Wilston specifically. These are not buyers who stumble across the suburb. They are family owner-occupiers and upsizers who have researched the area, understand the housing stock, and are waiting for the right property to come up. That commitment means genuine competition when a property is positioned well.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Wilston Village on Newmarket Road gives the suburb its retail and cafe anchor, and the proximity to McCook Park is a consistent drawcard for families. The suburb sits in a corridor where Windsor to the south and Lutwyche to the south-west have both seen strong buyer activity, and buyers who find those markets at their ceiling regularly move their attention to Wilston. Homes on the quieter residential streets away from Lutwyche Road attract the strongest competition, and original Queenslanders with intact character features routinely draw multiple-buyer interest at auction given how rarely they appear on the market.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Wilston Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Inner North Brisbane</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
